      "writtenOn": "2020-11-17T20:38:54Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Let\u0027s document about the contents of the buffer.\n\nSimplest would be to document that we *always* copy their data, so they can always mutate it after making the call. If we have a client that *really* wants us to \"share\" their buffer, we need to document when we actually do that.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 1537,
        "startChar": 10,
        "endLine": 1537,
        "endChar": 19
      },
      "revId": "a74d9dc9d1b0efa71ee4bf2ec01c5297568f149b",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "1d9a145a_0dc576ed",
        "filename": "modules/canvaskit/interface.js",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 1537,
      "author": {
        "id": 5395
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-11-17T20:43:15Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "As written, if they (intentionally; AFAIK, there\u0027s no way to accidentally do this) give us a TypedArray from a Malloc call, it will be shared, otherwise it will be copied. If you want, we can force a copy and just remove the sharing option from the table (since it wouldn\u0027t work for GPU textures anyway).",
      "parentUuid": "1e60fc9f_7659b0f5",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 1537,
        "startChar": 10,
        "endLine": 1537,
        "endChar": 19
